job_history.work_description: Successfully provided training and schedules, supervised, and guided my team through all aspects of recovery operations, in-process inspection/troubleshooting procedures, repairs and overhaul of all assigned wheeled vehicle mechanical and electrical components and systems.
Maintained and serviced aircraft engine, fuel, and lubrication systems. Handled and serviced aircraft ashore, or aboard a ship.
Maintained all 60 FA-18 Super Hornets up to U.S. Navy paint scheme and corrosion protection standards, without incident.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Successfully supervised and guided a team through recovery operations, repairs, and overhaul of wheeled vehicle components, indicating strong proficiency in leadership.

skills.name: Mechanical Maintenance
skills.explanation: Extensive experience in maintaining and servicing aircraft engine, fuel, and lubrication systems, as well as wheeled vehicle mechanical and electrical components, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Troubleshooting
skills.explanation: Handled in-process inspection and troubleshooting procedures for wheeled vehicle components, suggesting strong proficiency in troubleshooting.

skills.name: Electrical Systems
skills.explanation: Maintained and serviced electrical components of wheeled vehicles and aircraft, indicating strong proficiency in electrical systems.

skills.name: Project Management
skills.explanation: Coordinated and guided team through recovery operations and repairs, showing a solid working proficiency in project management.

skills.name: Information System Security
skills.explanation: Currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Information System Security, suggesting some familiarity with the subject.

skills.name: Network Administration
skills.explanation: Completed a certificate course in Network Administrator, indicating some practical experience in network administration.
